A few reminders for the game Saturday, Mart vs Anahuac at Madisonville provided by Madisonville:

1. NO tickets will be on sale at the gate. No passes or senior citizen passes will be accepted. All tickets must be purchased online at: https://www.madisonvillecisd.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=129355&type=d&pREC_ID=2052438&fbclid=IwAR2yPtkgFdbo4pGsq-tMFB46SB8HxwmUxdMalS8WQ0Tmz5QGpYcSbvb0FxA

2. The bleachers are marked with a fluorescent green tape and we made it simple to follow as our rule is DO NOT sit on any green tape and you will be vertically and horizontally spaced. We ask that all fans enter with a mask and wear it to their seat. When seated they may lower the mask for comfort as long as their 6 foot is not compromised by others that do not cohabitate with them. We ask that they mask up again anytime mobile in the stadium or anytime social distancing is compromised by the movement of others.

3. The tickets purchased by the fans may be printed and the QR code scanned or we have the ability to scan them phone to phone.

post_text:
Panther Family,
We are diligently working on plans for the new school year. We are still waiting on guidance from TEA on what safety measures must be followed, but we do know that we will open for the 2020-2021 school year.
However, parents that choose to keep their students at home out of COVID-19 concerns will be able to. A remote learning experience will be provided in that situation. In order to help us plan, we need to get an estimate on how many families are considering that option. We realize that you will need much more information before making a final decision, but if you plan on keeping your students at home and participating in remote learning, please email your campus principal with your student's name and grade level.
High School - beau.sanchez@mymartisd.org
Elementary School - amy.stone@mymartisd.org

Thank you,
Betsy Burnett
Superintendent

However, parents that choose to keep their students at home out of COVID-19 concerns will be able to. A remote learning experience will be provided in that situation. In order to help us plan, we need to get an estimate on how many families are considering that option. We realize that you will need much more information before making a final decision, but if you plan on keeping your students at home and participating in remote learning, please email your campus principal with your student's name and grade level.
High School - beau.sanchez@mymartisd.org
Elementary School - amy.stone@mymartisd.org

Thank you,
Betsy Burnett
Superintendent

Dear Panther Family,
Due to guidance and regulations provided by the State of Texas and TEA, the Mart High School Graduation ceremony for the Class of 2020 will be held on Friday, June 5 at 8pm. The ceremony will take place in-person on the football field. In order to plan appropriate social distancing measures, we need to attempt to get a count of those guests who wish to attend in person. Please submit the form below to help us with this count. The more accurate the count, the better we can plan for a smooth evening. The ceremony will also be live streamed and recorded in order to encourage only close family and friends to attend in person. This will also allow those in high risk populations to view from home. If you have any questions, please contact me at betsy.burnett@mymartisd.org.

Betsy Burnett
Superintendent
Mart ISD

post_text:
Dear Panther Family,
It is with great sadness that we announce that we will not be returning to campus for school this year. Governor Abbott issued the statewide decision early this afternoon. While we miss our students and colleagues terribly, we realize that the health and safety of our communities comes first. We will continue with our remote learning plan as scheduled through May 1, and arrange for the remaining 3 weeks of instruction on May 4. Decisions on other end of year activities will be released as they are made. Please do not hesitate to reach out to us if your family needs anything. We love you and wish you the best during this time of separation.

Sincerely,
Betsy Burnett
Superintendent

Due to the COVID-19 pandemic and the resulting ban of large gatherings, the MHS Prom on May 9th has been canceled.

Instead, please join us for:
Mart High School Homecoming Dance
“A Starry Evening”
Saturday, October 17th, 2020
8:00 to 11:00pm
Mart Community Center

Tickets are $10
And will be available in the Fall of 2020.

This dance is open to all 9th -12th grade students.
The Class of 2020 graduates will also be allowed to attend free of charge.
Semi-Formal / Formal attire is required.
This dance is in lieu of the May 9th prom.
Only 20-21 Juniors/Seniors & Graduates will be allowed to bring a guest from outside of Mart ISD. These guests will have to be approved by the high school office.

post_text:
Day 1 of meal delivery & pick up was a success!
There are a few changes we will make for the remainder of the week. Pick up will continue at the high school cafeteria from 9am-11am.
Both breakfast & lunch will be picked up at the same time. We can provide meals to any students ages 1-18 regardless of whether they attend Mart ISD.
Any family that does not have transportation, but that would still like to receive a meal, should fill out the form found at the link below. We understand that everyone may not have access to technology, so please help us spread the word. Delivery can also be arranged by calling Betsy Burnett at (254) 722-3793.
*Please do not ask for delivery by commenting below or through Facebook messenger- as these comments are sometimes hard to track and we don't want to miss anyone! The preferred communication is through the link below.
Thank you for your continued patience.

**If you share this post, please make sure to share the original message so that the meal pick up information is shared also.*

https://forms.gle/cTjZwZqvvwicQk4SA

post_text: Update- we have just been notified that the student in question has been arrested. However, heightened security will remain in place for the remainder of the week.
shared_text:
Mart Independent School District
January 8 at 8:32 PM ·

Update 8:58pm, we have just been notified that the student in question has been arrested. However, heightened security will remain in place for the remainder of the week.

The safety and security of our students and staff is always our top priority, and we take all threats seriously. As such, we feel it’s important that we make you aware of a terroristic threat made by a Mart High student on social media. Upon learning of the threat, we immediately followed our school safety protocols and contacted local authorities. Local authorities are continuing to investigate and the identified student will face student discipline measures. As an extra measure of precaution, Mart ISD will have extra police patrols and presence around the school in addition to our standard safety measures. We ask our families to discuss the day’s events with their child and emphasize the seriousness of this issue. Please contact me if you have any questions or concerns.

post_text:
This is what it's all about! I am so proud of our Panthers and the young men they are when everyone is watching - and when they aren't.

I received the following email this weekend from a Falls City parent:

Good evening. My name is Beth Kelley, and I am from Falls City, TX. I have 2 daughters. One is on the Color Guard team, and the other is on our dance team. I want to bring to your attention that I just now noticed as I was watching videos, and looking at the photos from our match up Friday night. Our team, and community watched our boys release the raw sadness of losing this game, and they were crying, and hugging, and just defeated. Just in the background behind our team, some of your football players, and staff took out the time that they didn’t have to, and came over, and lifted our boys and community up. That really made an impact on us. Please watch this video, and share it with your team, and staff. They need to know what it meant to us. Thank you, and good luck on Thursday in Arlington. GO PANTHERS!!!

post_text: This afternoon around 4pm, an exhaust fan caught fire in a restroom between two of the current high school classrooms. The few students on campus were immediately evacuated from the area, and a fire extinguisher was used to put out the flames. The Mart VFD responded and thoroughly checked the building for any other issues. At this time, it does not appear that any damage was done to the building. Classes will be held as regularly scheduled tomorrow.

shared_text:
Mart High School Band
July 13, 2019 at 5:06 PM ·

Dear Goin’ Band From Pantherland!!!!!

My name is Conrad Flusche and I am the new band Director in Mart!!! I am extremely excited to be your band director!!!! A few things about myself:

This will be my 20th year to teach.
I’ve spent the last 6 years in Mexia as the head director.
I live in the country.
I am a hard worker and want to help you become the best band you can be!!! My goal is to get you a sweepstakes.

I know many of you have been wondering about this upcoming year!!!

Our show is “Lost at Sea”.
We will start drill probably the 13th.
You will be able to pick up music anytime I’m up there!
I will post when I am when I’m at the band hall.
All Region music will be ready at summer band.
When I get Centex music I will have it ready.
I’m very excited that we get to perform and help our football team win another state title!!!!!

Mrs. Smith and Mrs. King have been a great help in preparing for the upcoming year!!!!

I have attached the schedule for summer band!!!

Please let me know if you need anything!!! I am here to help you!!!

Thank You

Conrad Flusche

post_text:
Mart Lions Club will host a pancake dinner on Friday, September 28th. The dinner will begin at 5:00 and the varsity football team will play Refugio in Mart at 7:30. Not only will the dinner benefit the local chapter of the Lions Club, but 50% of the proceeds from the night will be donated to Refugio ISD as they continue to recover from Hurricane Harvey. Their administrative offices are still located in the hallways of the school, and the school internet was just restored a couple of weeks ago. They lost many permanent records during the flooding and some of their students are still displaced from their homes. Let's show Refugio that Mart supports them in their rebuilding efforts!
Tickets are $9 each and can be purchased at the elementary and high school offices.
The deadline to purchase tickets is today! Call us to reserve yours!

post_text: This is a great opportunity for community service if any students are interested!
shared_text:
First United Methodist Church of Mart
July 10, 2018 at 2:46 PM ·

IT’S VBS TIME!! Vacation Bible School will run from Sunday, July 22 to Thursday, July 26 from 5:30-8:00pm each night (doors open at 5). The kids are served dinner and will have a full schedule of worship, music, bible, story time, mission experience, games, and crafts! Remember we will be taking an offering each evening (pennies to bills) and give it to whichever mission the kids vote on at the end of the week. We are so excited to have the opportunity to welcome returning children and new ones. VBS is open to ALL kids, age 4 years old to 8th grade. We welcome parents to join us for opening worship each evening at 5:30pm. Our theme is “Shipwrecked”. We have all hands on deck and are ready to take this adventure with your kiddos as we explore and learn all of the ways Jesus “rescues” us! For information or pre-registration, call the church at 254-876-2751.
